{#
  Reusable panel-title tooltip. Import as a macro:

      {% from "_panel_help.html.jinja" import panel_help %}
      {{ panel_help("Light curve", caller) }}

  The body is provided by the caller block — use {% call panel_help("…") %}
  and put <ul>/<p> etc. inside. Shows on hover or keyboard focus; positioned
  absolutely below the title with z-50 so it overlays sibling panels.

  `side` = "left" (default) or "right" anchors the tooltip's horizontal edge —
  right-edge panels use "right" so the card doesn't overflow the viewport.
#}
{#
  Why position:fixed instead of position:absolute?

  The detail-view grid rows (`detail-row-1`, `detail-row-2`) use
  `overflow:hidden` so the row-resize handle can shrink them without
  bleeding into the other row. That clips every descendant — including
  absolutely-positioned tooltips. With `position:absolute`, only the
  panels whose slots themselves have `overflow:auto` (Basic Information)
  let the user reach the tooltip's bottom; every other panel's tooltip
  was silently clipped, scrollbar and all.

  `position:fixed` escapes every overflow ancestor by being positioned
  relative to the viewport — but viewport-relative also means we have
  to compute `top`/`left` ourselves on each show. A small inline script
  reads the trigger's `getBoundingClientRect()` and updates the tooltip
  before fade-in. `group-hover`/`group-focus-within` still drive
  visibility, so keyboard focus and pointer hover both work.
#}
{% macro panel_help(title, side="left") %}
<div class="tw-relative tw-group panel-help" data-tooltip-side="{{ side }}">
  <div class="tw-text-text-secondary tw-text-xs tw-uppercase tw-cursor-help tw-underline tw-decoration-dotted tw-underline-offset-2" tabindex="0">
    {{ title }} <span class="tw-text-text-muted tw-normal-case">(?)</span>
  </div>
  <div
    role="tooltip"
    class="tw-hidden group-hover:tw-block group-focus-within:tw-block tw-fixed tw-z-50 tw-w-80 tw-max-w-[calc(100vw-2rem)] tw-max-h-[80vh] tw-overflow-y-auto tw-bg-bg-card tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-p-3 tw-text-xs tw-text-text-primary tw-normal-case tw-shadow-lg tw-leading-relaxed"
  >
    {{ caller() }}
  </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}
